results.t: FANCY definition and meaning | Collins English Dictionary

results.p: 1. a : a liking formed by caprice rather than reason : inclination took a fancy to the mutt b : amorous fondness : love She took a fancy to the young man.

results.t: FANCY | definition in the Cambridge English Dictionary
results.p: to be sexually attracted to someone: He could tell she fancied him. fancy yourself UK disapproving to think you are very attractive or important.
adjective · ornamental; decorative; not plain: · tending or intending to impress: fancy four-syllable words. · complicated or difficult to perform or execute:.
Fancy can be an adjective, noun, or a verb. As an adjective, it's the opposite of plain. The noun names something that isn't real.
